Luckily, this is a solved problem for go.<p><pre><code>  func helper(a float64, c chan float64){
      time.Sleep(time.Duration(a) * time.Second)
      c &lt;- a
  }

  func clamp(a float64, min float64, max float64) float64 {
      c := make(chan  float64, 3)
      go helper(a, c)
      go helper(min, c)
      go helper(max, c)
      _, out, _ := &lt;-c, &lt;-c, &lt;-c
      return out
  }</code></pre>

The basic function is simply defined as:<p><pre><code>  function clamp(num, min, max) {
    return Math.max(min, Math.min(num, max));
  }
</code></pre>
That is, if you don&#x27;t try to do anything fancy and make any parameters optional. Lodash does and it makes the implementation much more complex.<p><pre><code>  _.clamp(input: number, lower?: number, upper: number): number;
</code></pre>
